comments: Dedmon (MIA) makes clean hand-on-ball contact to deflect the post entry pass away from Embiid (PHI) and out of bounds. The ball is correctly awarded to the 76ers.
Robinson (MIA) and Green (PHI) mutually engage and disengage, and marginal contact occurs during the rebound.

Maxey (PHI) jumps into and makes contact with Lowry's (MIA) body, which affects his driving shot attempt. Any follow-through contact between Lowry and Embiid (PHI) after they return to the ground is deemed incidental.
Green (PHI) cleanly deflects the pass away from Lowry (MIA) and steals the ball.
Robinson (MIA) is in the paint for less than three seconds when he is imminently actively guarding an opponent.
Dedmon (MIA) establishes himself in a legal guarding position outside the restricted area and absorbs the contact from Harris (PHI) at the end of his drive.
Dedmon (MIA) establishes himself in a screening position in Maxey's (PHI) path and absorbs the contact on the pick.
Tucker (MIA) briefly places his hands on Maxey's (PHI) side, and marginal contact occurs as he releases toward the basket after slipping the pick.
Harris (PHI) legally contests Lowry's (MIA) jump shot attempt.  Any "high-five" contact after the release is considered incidental.
Green (PHI) contests the shot and then moves away from Vincent (MIA) to avoid any foot-to-foot contact as he returns to the ground after his jump shot attempt.
Curry (PHI) jumps toward and extends both hands into Vincent's (MIA) front after his release, which affects his follow-through.
Dedmon (MIA) is bringing his arm into a vertical position as he absorbs the marginal contact initiated by Embiid (PHI) when he swings the ball toward the hoop on his post-shot attempt.
Green (PHI) reaches for the ball and avoids contact with Lowry's (PHI) arm as he brings the ball up the court.
Dedmon (MIA) could be deemed to be imminently exiting the lane within three seconds.
Green (PHI) maintains a legal guarding position on Lowry (MIA) and makes clean ball contact to poke it loose.
Vincent (MIA) regains control of the loose ball before stepping on the midcourt line and a backcourt violation is correctly called.
Dedmon (MIA) makes clean hand on ball contact as he tries to deflect the inbounds pass away from Embiid (PHI).
Dedmon (MIA) legally contests Embiid's (PHI) jump shot attempt.
Green (PHI) disengages from Robinson's (MIA) boxout and makes contact with Lowry's (MIA) body by jumping into him, which dislodges him to the ground.
